<div id="review_719229662" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/719229662" />
    <a title="Radostinski" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23896869-radostinski"><img alt="Radostinski" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1379071675p2/23896869.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/719229662?book_show_action=true">Sep 14, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Radostinski" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Radostinski" href="/user/show/23896869-radostinski">Radostinski</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/23896869-radostinski?shelf=e-books">e-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/23896869-radostinski?shelf=english-language">english-language</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/23896869-radostinski?shelf=communism">communism</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer719229662" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11104706866934046813">This is probably one of the most important books on the Soviet Union. If you are interested in its degeneration and the future collapse of the Eastern block, this is the perfect book to start with. As was the case with the most genuine revolutionaries, Trotsky tended to overestimate the revolutionary potential of the masses. In this book he professes that either there will be a new workers&apos; revolution or capitalism will be restored in Russia. Well, guess what happened at the end. </span>
  <span id="freeText11104706866934046813" style="display:none">This is probably one of the most important books on the Soviet Union. If you are interested in its degeneration and the future collapse of the Eastern block, this is the perfect book to start with. As was the case with the most genuine revolutionaries, Trotsky tended to overestimate the revolutionary potential of the masses. In this book he professes that either there will be a new workers' revolution or capitalism will be restored in Russia. Well, guess what happened at the end. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11104706866934046813" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
