<span id="freeTextContainer16921112483128738561">A scathing critique of Stalin&apos;s regime in its early days and prescient prediction of the fate of the &quot;Soviet&quot; Union and the fate of Europe. Trotsky writes with a sharp wit, sarcastic rhetoric and amiable arrogance at times, however this does lead to some self indulgent meanderings at times.<br/>A must-read for anyone interested in Left politics as a cautionary tale about the dangers of the revolution and what can be done to prevent them when the time comes!<br/>This book serves very well as a sequel to Or</span>
